# Jenkins Job

A Jenkins Job is an automation task executed by Jenkins. It can be used for building code, testing, creating Docker images, deploying applications, or running scripts. In modern CI/CD environments, Pipeline jobs are preferred because the entire workflow is defined as code in a Jenkinsfile, making it version-controlled and reusable.

# Type of Jenkins triggers

The common Jenkins triggers are Manual Trigger, SCM Polling, Webhook Trigger, Build Periodically (cron schedule), Remote Trigger via API, and Upstream/Downstream Triggers. In production, webhook-based triggering from Git repositories is preferred because it starts builds immediately when code is pushed and avoids the overhead of polling.

# Jenkins Weather Icon Meaning

The Weather Icon in Jenkins indicates the health of a job based on last 5 build results.

Weather Icon Build Health
☀️ Sunny 80%–100% successful builds
🌤️ Partly Sunny 60%–79% successful builds
☁️ Cloudy 40%–59% successful builds
🌧️ Rainy 20%–39% successful builds
⛈️ Stormy 0%–19% successful builds

